oai_dc:dc.dc:title: RESEARCH FOR THE COASTAL AREA OF THE DELTA REGION OF THE NETHERLANDS
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Dronkers, J.J.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Netherlands
Netherlands delta
coast research
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Tidal computations, wave studies, refraction computations, and morphological studies are discussed and practical results are mentioned Theoretical investigations on refraction computations, in particular the accuracy, are dealt with in detail, because difficulties occurred in the practical applications A former study of Morra, based on Kalinske's work on sand transport, has also been discussed in some detail in the section on morphological studies.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Coastal Engineering Proceedings; No. 12 (1970): Proceedings of 12th Conference on Coastal Engineering, Washington, D.C., 1970.; 108
